    <name>
      <text>Finding Possible Values of a Given Distance between Points</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Given that the distance between points \(P\) and \(Q\) with coordinates \(({@x_cord_1@},a)\) and \(({@x_cord_2@},{@y_cord_2@})\) respectively is \({@dist@}\) units, find the possible values of \(a\). 
<em>Note: Give your answers in exact form. In the case of one solution, repeat the same solution in the two inputs.</em></p>
<p>\(a=\)[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] or \(a=\)[[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3><b>Worked Solution</b></h3>
<p>We recall the formula of the distance given by \(PQ= \displaystyle \sqrt{(x_{q}-x_{p})^{2}+(y_{q}-y_{p})^{2}} \). Since \(PQ={@dist@}\), we have;</p>
<p>\( \begin{align}
\sqrt{({@x_cord_2@}-{@x_cord_1@})^2+({@y_cord_2@}-{@y_cord_1@})^2} &={@dist@}\\
({@x_cord_2-x_cord_1@})^2+({@y_cord_2@}-{@y_cord_1@})^2 &={@dist^2@}\\
({@y_cord_2@}-{@y_cord_1@})^2 & ={@dist^2-(x_cord_2-x_cord_1)^2@}
\end{align}
\)</p>
[[ if test='discr_a1>0' ]]
<p>\({@y_cord_2@}-{@y_cord_1@}= \sqrt{{@dist^2-(x_cord_2-x_cord_1)^2@}}\) or \({@y_cord_2@}-{@y_cord_1@}= -\sqrt{{@dist^2-(x_cord_2-x_cord_1)^2@}}\)</p>
<p>\(a={@ta2@}\) or \(a={@ta3@}\)</p>
[[ elif test='discr_a1=0' ]]
<p>\({@y_cord_2@}-{@y_cord_1@}=\sqrt{{@dist^2-(x_cord_2-x_cord_1)^2@}}\)</p>
<p>\(a={@ta1@}\)</p>
[[ else ]]
The system has no solution
[[/ if]]]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
